name: "Outsider's Perspective" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Brush pen, paint pen, metallic marker, and colored pencil on reclaimed cardboard with digital embellishments and color.] The ritual was in full performance. I watched, completely unaware of what was taking place, but enjoying the spectacle nonetheless! (Sometimes, you just have to roll will it...) ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
